<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1575,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,428,1683,1708]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Description. Adult.</emphasis>
Colouration. Male dark brown or black, with straw-coloured patches on vertex medially and anteriorly, on the pronotum in the middle, on the mesopraescutum postero-laterally and on the mesoscutum medially, laterally and caudally. Head ventrally, clypeus, mesoscutellum, metascutum medially and thorax laterally along a narrow band whitish. Scape brown. Legs with femora brown basally, straw-coloured apically, dark colour more expanded on meso and metafemora; pro and mesotibiae and tarsi brownish, metatibia and tarsus yellowish, apical tarsal segments darker than basal one. Forewing whitish, transparent, veins brown. Hindwing whitish. Female light brown dorsally, whitish ventrally, almost completely lacking dark brown or black except for antennal flagellum, a few small patches on pleura of thorax and tip of terminalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1575,2032]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1436,151,575]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="7" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Structure. Anterior head margin, in dorsal view, forming wide 'U'-shaped cleft between large toruli. Antenna 
<number box="[151,262,2007,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.115" valueMax="4.34" valueMin="3.89">3.89–4.34</number>
times as long as head width, segment 
<number box="[693,707,2007,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="3.0">3</number>
<number box="[714,798,2007,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.2999999999999998" valueMax="1.4" valueMin="1.2">1.2–1.4</number>
times as long as segment 
<number box="[1091,1108,2007,2031]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.0">4</number>
. Forewing (
<figureCitation box="[1241,1308,2007,2032]" captionStart="FIGURES 3 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,269,1911,1934]" captionTargetBox="[154,1433,272,1882]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,267,1887]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 3 – 11. Forewing of Mastigimas spp. 3. M. anjosi. 4. M. cedrelae. 5. M. colombianus sp. n. 6. M. drepanodis sp. n. 7, 11. M. ernstii. 8. M. peruanus. 9. M. reseri sp. n. 10. M. schwarzi. 11. Pterostigma length = a, length of line between apices of pterostigma and vein Rs = b. Scale bar = 0.5 mm for figs 3 – 10." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285263/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Fig. 
<number box="[1294,1308,2007,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
) 
<number box="[1324,1437,2007,2032]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="4.5649999999999995" valueMax="4.61" valueMin="4.52">4.52–4.61</number>
times as long as head width, 
<number box="[476,588,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.635" valueMax="2.68" valueMin="2.59">2.59–2.68</number>
times as long wide, pterostigma long and narrow, ratio a/b 
<number box="[1256,1342,152,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.9500000000000001" valueMax="1.1" valueMin="0.8">0.8–1.1</number>
, cell cu 
<number box="[1428,1436,166,180]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
moderately high. Male proctiger 
<number box="[535,584,190,215]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.36">0.36</number>
times as long as head width. Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[1065,1156,190,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 12 – 19" captionStartId="5.[151,269,1080,1103]" captionTargetBox="[151,1420,194,1059]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,194,1059]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 12 – 19. Male paramere, in profile, of Mastigimas spp. 12. M. anjosi. 13. M. cedrelae. 14. M. colombianus sp. n. 15. M. drepanodis sp. n. 16. M. ernstii. 17. M. peruanus. 18. M. reseri sp. n. 19. M. schwarzi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285264/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs 14</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1172,1201,191,215]" captionStart="FIGURES 20 – 27" captionStartId="6.[151,269,1684,1707]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,630,1662]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[154,1433,630,1662]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 20 – 27. Inner face of male paramere, in profile, of Mastigimas spp. 20. M. anjosi. 21. M. cedrelae. 22. M. colombianus sp. n. 23. M. drepanodis sp. n. 24. M. ernstii. 25. M. peruanus. 26. M. reseri sp. n. 27. M. schwarzi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285265/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">22</figureCitation>
) bifid, with narrow, rounded outer lobe and claw-like inner lobe. Distal portion of aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1097,226,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,269,1727,1750]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,878,1705]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,878,1706]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Distal portion of aedeagus of Mastigimas spp. 28. M. anjosi. 29. M. cedrelae. 30. M. colombianus sp. n. 31. M. drepanodis sp. n. 32. M. ernstii. 33. M. peruanus. 34. M. reseri sp. n. 35. M. schwarzi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285266/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1068,1097,227,251]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
) less than a third as long as segment, with small apical hook. Female terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[757,841,262,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 36 – 43" captionStartId="10.[151,269,1977,2000]" captionTargetBox="[186,1406,195,1951]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[186,1406,195,1951]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 36 – 43. Female terminalia, in profile, of Mastigimas spp. 36. M. anjosi. 37. M. cedrelae. 38. M. colombianus sp. n. 39. M. drepanodis sp. n. 40. M. ernstii. 41. M. peruanus. 42. M. reseri sp. n. 43. M. schwarzi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/285267/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[812,841,263,287]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="38.0">38</number>
</figureCitation>
) short; dorsal outline of proctiger strongly concave; proctiger 
<number box="[259,308,299,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="0.94">0.94</number>
times as long as head width, and 
<number box="[685,734,299,323]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.43">2.43</number>
times as long as subgenital plate.
</paragraph>
